<item>
            <title>[DERBY-6592] Update the version of ant which we tell new developers to use.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-6592</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The top level BUILDING.html page tells users to grab ant version 1.7.0 or higher. I don&apos;t know whether that version still works. I have been using version 1.9.2 for a long time. I see no harm in changing the instructions to tell new developers to grab ant version 1.9.2. I think it&apos;s a good idea to update these instructions regularly.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
