                            <comment id="14013822" author="rhillegas" created="Fri, 30 May 2014 16:43:44 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching derby-6592-01-aa-updateAntVersion.diff. This patch updates the version of ant which we tell new developers to use.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Touches the following file:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;M       BUILDING.html&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14013874" author="chaase3" created="Fri, 30 May 2014 17:10:10 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;While you&apos;re at it, you could make a similar fix on this page:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://db.apache.org/derby/manuals/dita.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://db.apache.org/derby/manuals/dita.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It mentions Ant 1.6.2! And JDK 1.4.2 ... You could just change it to &quot;any supported JDK version&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have to admit I&apos;m still using Ant 1.8.2.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sadly, we&apos;re still stuck with ancient DITA.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14013991" author="rhillegas" created="Fri, 30 May 2014 18:42:56 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for pointing out that stale information on our website, Kim. That page is certainly pretty dusty. I&apos;ll clean that up, along with some other cruft on that page (like the references to monohtml) and I&apos;ll add the new Security Guide to the list of manuals on the page.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;By the way, how do you navigate to that page? I couldn&apos;t figure out how to get there starting from the landing page at &lt;a href=&quot;http://db.apache.org/derby&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://db.apache.org/derby&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks,&lt;br/&gt;
-Rick&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14013993" author="chaase3" created="Fri, 30 May 2014 18:46:02 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, Rick! &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;First you click the Documentation tab and then you click &quot;DITA Source&quot; in the left menu. There may be more cruft in that area besides that topic. Ooh, for instance, the Writing Guidelines topic still mentions &quot;Working with Derby&quot;. (It was done by Laura Stewart way back when.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14014006" author="rhillegas" created="Fri, 30 May 2014 18:51:15 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Maybe as a summer project, we should march through the whole website, a tab at a time, and freshen it up.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14014089" author="rhillegas" created="Fri, 30 May 2014 19:45:25 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching derby-6592-02-aa-ditaInstructionsCleanup.diff. This freshens up various stale bits on the website dita instructions page.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Touches the following files:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;X       build/site&lt;br/&gt;
M       src/documentation/content/xdocs/manuals/dita.xml&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Performing status on external item at &apos;build/site&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
