                            <comment id="14026428" author="chaase3" created="Tue, 10 Jun 2014 14:23:37 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I just found another out-of-date link on the DITA page, &lt;a href=&quot;http://db.apache.org/derby/manuals/dita.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://db.apache.org/derby/manuals/dita.html&lt;/a&gt;. The 5th bullet links to a chapter in the 1.1 version of the Subversion docs &amp;#8211; which are now up to version 1.7. It might be better to make the link go to the top-level &lt;a href=&quot;http://svnbook.red-bean.com/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://svnbook.red-bean.com/&lt;/a&gt; and make the text more precise: &quot;more information is in the Properties section of the Subversion documentation&quot;. The section has moved from Chapter 7 to Chapter 3 over the years, and may continue to migrate.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
